President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts, including Chai R. Feldblum as Commissioner of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission, Carmen Lomellin as Permanent Representative of the United States of America to the Organization of American States, Frederick "Rick" Barton as Representative of the United States of America on the Economic and Social Council of the United Nations, Jide Zeitlin as Representative of the United States of America to the United Nations for U.N. Management and Reform, and Charles Collyns as Assistant Secretary for International Finance at the Department of the Treasury. President Obama also appointed seven board members to the Federal Service Impasses Panel (FSIP).